pesticide.PPE: Long-sleeved shirt and long pants; Shoes plus socks; Chemical-resistant gloves such as Barrier Laminate, Butyl Rubber ≥14 mils, Nitrile Rubber ≥14 mils, Neoprene Rubber ≥14 mils, Natural Rubber ≥14 mils, Polyethylene, Polyvinyl Chloride (PVC) ≥14 mils or Viton ≥14 mils.

Active_Ingredients.name: Thiamethoxam
Active_Ingredients.mode_Of_Action: Systemic insecticide; neonicotinoid (nicotinic acetylcholine receptor agonist)

Active_Ingredients.name: Thiabendazole
Active_Ingredients.mode_Of_Action: Methyl-benzimidazole carbamate; disrupts β-tubulin assembly in mitosis

Active_Ingredients.name: Mefenoxam
Active_Ingredients.mode_Of_Action: Phenylamide; interferes with fungal RNA synthesis

Active_Ingredients.name: Tebuconazole
Active_Ingredients.mode_Of_Action: Triazole; demethylation inhibitor of sterol biosynthesis

Safety_Information.general_Info: CAUTION. Avoid contact with eyes, skin or clothing. Avoid breathing vapor or spray mist.
Safety_Information.if_In_Eyes: Hold eye open and rinse slowly and gently with water for 15-20 minutes. Remove contact lenses, if present, after the first 5 minutes, then continue rinsing. Call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice.
Safety_Information.if_Swallowed: Call a poison control center or doctor immediately for treatment advice. Have person sip a glass of water if able to swallow. Do not induce vomiting unless told to by a poison control center or doctor. Do not give anything by mouth to an unconscious person.
Safety_Information.if_On_Skin: Take off contaminated clothing. Rinse skin immediately with plenty of water for 15-20 minutes. Call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice.
Safety_Information.if_Inhaled: Move person to fresh air. If person is not breathing, call 911 or an ambulance, then give artificial respiration, preferably mouth-to-mouth if possible. Call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice.
Safety_Information.physician_Note: Have the product container or label with you when calling poison control center or doctor or going for treatment. For 24-Hour Emergency Assistance spill, leak, fire, exposure, or accident call CHEMTREC 1-800-424-9300
